news.title: Cochin development body seeks team for land pooling for Infopark Phase III
news.para: The Greater Cochin Development Authority (GCDA) is collaborating with the district collector to form a special revenue team for land pooling, essential for Infopark's Phase III expansion. Following approval for the project spanning over 300 acres, GCDA seeks support from revenue officials, including surveyors and legal experts, to initiate the land pooling process.

news.title: Technopark unveils masterplan for phase IV; Kerala bets big on IT to compete with top tech hubs
news.para: Technopark's Phase IV expansion, branded Technocity, is set to transform Thiruvananthapuram into a global IT hub. The 389-acre integrated IT city, designed with a walk-to-work model, aims to attract GCCs, emerging tech firms, and R&D investments. This initiative is part of Kerala's strategy to compete with established IT centers and boost its economy by focusing on next-generation industries.

news.title: Interarch Building Solutions commissions phase-II of unit in Andhra Pradesh
news.para: Interarch Building Solutions has launched the second phase of its Andhra Pradesh facility, increasing PEB manufacturing capacity by 25,000 MT annually with a Rs 32 crore investment. Additionally, a new Box Column Line has been commissioned in Uttarakhand, boosting production by 15,000 MT per annum with a Rs 21 crore investment. This expansion targets sectors like renewables, automobiles, and FMCG.

news.title: Land data to be digitised with ownership rights
news.para: The government is set to establish a comprehensive electronic land record database, encompassing both rural and urban areas, complete with cadastral maps. This initiative aims to enhance real-time information flow, optimize land resource utilization, reduce disputes, and improve transparency. The move is crucial for pursuing land reforms to stimulate economic growth.

news.title: Banks to lend more to the rich to push mortgage growth
news.para: Banks are strategically targeting the luxury housing market to boost mortgage growth, offering tailored loan products to affluent buyers seeking premium properties in major cities and suburbs. This segment is experiencing significant growth, driven by demand for larger, more luxurious homes. Banks view these high-end loans as opportunities to establish long-term relationships and cross-sell other financial products.

news.title: New city corporations in Bengaluru get ₹125 crore shot in the arm
news.para: The Karnataka government has sanctioned Rs 125 crore for Bengaluru's five new city corporations, recently formed from the BBMP restructuring. Each corporation will receive Rs 25 crore for operational expenses until direct tax remittance is established. This temporary funding, drawn from BBMP property tax collections, ensures uninterrupted civic services during the transition under the Greater Bengaluru Administration Act-2024.

news.title: E-registration from builders’ office gains traction in Maharashtra
news.para: Maharashtra's online property registration system, allowing developers to register first-sale properties, has gained significant traction, reducing congestion at sub-registrar offices. Over 11,000 documents have been registered since 2023, with nearly 4,000 in the current financial year.

news.title: Illegal colonies on 155-acre prime Noida airport plots razed
news.para: Yamuna Expressway Industrial Development Authority (YEIDA) intensified its crackdown on illegal colonies near Noida International Airport, reclaiming 155 acres of land worth ₹2,500 crore in Bulandshahr. This action follows reports of land mafias deceiving homebuyers with promises of prime airport plots.

news.title: Gurugram court rejects bail plea of Ocean Seven Buildtech's ex-CEO in ₹5.7 crore fraud case
news.para: A Gurugram court denied anticipatory bail to former Ocean Seven Buildtech CEO Sanjeev Kumar in a Rs 5.7 crore cheating and forgery case. The complainant, Amit Rastogi, alleged that Kumar induced his family to invest Rs 2.8 crore in 2013 with promises of high returns, which were never fulfilled.

news.title: SEBI rents apartment in Mumbai’s Prabhadevi for chairman at ₹7 lakh per month
news.para: SEBI has leased a luxurious 5-bedroom apartment in Mumbai's Prabhadevi for its Chairman, Tuhin Kanta Pandey, at a monthly rent of Rs 7 lakh. The lease agreement, effective from September 3, 2025, includes four car parks and a 5% annual rent escalation. This deal reflects the strong demand in Mumbai's luxury housing market.

news.title: CCI okays PNC Infratech's proposal to acquire debt-ridden Jaiprakash Associates
news.para: The CCI has granted in-principle approval to PNC Infratech's proposed acquisition of debt-ridden Jaiprakash Associates, contingent on a successful bid in the ongoing insolvency proceeding. This approval is crucial following a Supreme Court ruling mandating CCI clearance before resolution plan voting. JAL, facing claims of over Rs 57,000 crore, owns significant real estate, cement plants, and investments in subsidiaries.

news.title: CCI approves acquisition of up to 75% shareholding in Akzo Nobel India by JSW Paints
news.para: The Competition Commission of India (CCI) has approved the acquisition of up to 75% shareholding in Akzo Nobel India Limited (Target) by JSW Paints Limited (Acquirer), a release said.

news.title: Mahindra Lifespaces to redevelop two societies in Chembur, Mumbai
news.para: Mahindra Lifespace Developers is set to redevelop two housing societies in Mumbai's Chembur area, specifically in Diamond Garden. These projects, spanning 2.6 acres and 1.8 acres respectively, hold a combined gross development potential of approximately ₹1,700 crore.

news.title: Orissa HC junks LIC's decision to cancel flat allotments in Bhubaneswar
news.para: The Orissa High Court has overturned LIC's cancellation of flat allotments under its housing scheme in Bhubaneswar, directing the corporation to complete the process within eight weeks. This decision came after petitioners challenged LIC's switch to a public auction model, citing legal hurdles. The court balanced the interests by ordering allotments with an additional 10% payment from the original allottees.

news.title: Chhattisgarh: Consumer forum directs builder to buy back plot at double the price
news.para: The Chhattisgarh State Consumer Disputes Redressal Commission has directed a builder to repurchase a plot at double the original price from a consumer, Dayawati Chauhan, due to unfair trade practices and deficiency in service.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body announces new rules for ready-mix concrete plants
news.para: The Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation has mandated permits for all ready-mix concrete (RMC) plants, both on-site and off-site, operating within city limits. Commercial RMC plants are now restricted to industrial, agricultural, and logistical zones, while on-site plants are limited to construction sites. This decision, made to combat air pollution, requires plants to relocate from residential areas and obtain necessary clearances.

news.title: Telangana government eyes over ₹2,000 crore per acre in Raidurg land auction
news.para: Telangana government plans to auction two land parcels in Raidurg Knowledge City. The auction aims to generate over Rs 2,000 crore. The base price is set at Rs 101 crore per acre. The e-auction is scheduled for October 6. The location is near major companies and has good connectivity. Successful bidders must pay within 90 days.

news.title: Can’t deny housing society membership to homebuyers over builder’s default: HC
news.para: The Bombay High Court has ruled that a housing society cannot deny membership to flat purchasers based on a developer's non-compliance with the development agreement. Justice Amit Borkar directed a Vile Parle society to grant membership to 17 flat purchasers, emphasizing that membership eligibility is determined by cooperative society laws, rules, and bye-laws, not external contracts.

news.title: Stuck for 20 years, new firm may take over mall plot in Ghaziabad
news.para: Ghaziabad Development Authority is poised to transfer a 46,000sqm plot near Shaheed Sthal New Bus Adda metro station to Sakshi Fincap Private Ltd, after the initial developer, Celebration City, defaulted on payments for a mall project two decades ago.
